            "question": "What is a vaginal yeast infection?",
            "answer": "<p>Candida albicans is the most common type of yeast infection-related fungus, and naturally occurs as a healthy part of our bodies. For the most part, it's harmless. But when our vaginal biome becomes unbalanced, Candida takes over and causes what we refer to as a yeast infection. Common symptoms of a yeast infection include vulvar/vaginal itching, burning, painful urination, inflammation, pain during sex, and a thick, white discharge.</p>"
